corpus linguistics to improve language teaching and learning . ^ readily available korean-language corpora and easy-to-use tools can now be used on the spot in a language teaching context , by teachers and learners without extensive training in computational linguistics , and studies of linguistic features can be tailored to specific pedagogic context and learning requirements . ^ the  ame  ame institute workshop ' corpus linguistics for korean language learning and  ame ' will acquaint participants with the basic concepts of corpus linguistics , including corpus construction and  ame , concordancing , frequency counts and ranks , grammatical tagging , and related concepts . ^ participants will learn how to access korean corpora and how to use the available computer programs for korean corpus analysis . ^ the workshop will outline techniques for the teacher to use in materials preparation and curriculum design and for the individual learner to use in exploring meaning , structure , and use in korean . ^ in the second part of the workshop , participants will engage in individual projects chosen with their own learning goals in mind . ^ the deadline for applications is  ame  um ,  um ^ for more information or to apply , visit : ^  ebsite ^ * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * ^ southeast asian pedagogy workshops ^  ame  um  ebsite ^ a series of teacher training workshops will be conducted for faculty teaching at advanced study abroad programs in southeast  ame . ^ workshops are being planned for filipino , indonesian ,  ame ,  ame , and vietnamese . ^ training may also be conducted at the southeast asian studies  ame institute at the university of  ame . ^ visit our website for more information and updates . ^ a national foreign language resource center  har university of  ame'  har  har  um  ame road , #  um  har  ame hi  um c voice : ( 80 miley  um , fax : ( 80 miley  um email :  mail visit our website   ^  ebsite </text_normal><